&lt;p&gt;Note: I&apos;ve used &lt;tt&gt;int&lt;/tt&gt; to sum internally but return a &lt;tt&gt;byte&lt;/tt&gt; to be consistent with the other types. Related: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9674&quot; title=&quot;Reevaluate size of result/accumulator types of built in sum()+avg() functions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-9674&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-9674&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT: when reviewing, also check the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/snazy/cassandra/tree/9671-aggr-tiny-small-trunk&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;merge-to-trunk branch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14620822" author="snazy" created="Thu, 9 Jul 2015 16:46:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Strike the note about internal sum+accumulator types.&lt;br/&gt;
sum+avg in this patch use types &lt;tt&gt;byte&lt;/tt&gt; resp. &lt;tt&gt;short&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
Force-pushed an update of the branches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
